                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "Are we talking backtesting, in which case, connections aren't relevant, or live processing, in which case you wouldn't get up to 2000 each for WIN or PLACE markets?\n\nIf you're talking live processing then running separate instances of Flumine to achieve separate connections means that you won't be able to link different markets from the same event as they won't be on the same instance."
