        "text": "In that case, I think you're way overthinking this. If you're going to process each market individually, then it doesn't really matter how you split them across connections. Sure there are some minor load balancing differences depending on volume of data in different markets and the processing time for the associated strategies them, but they are all comprehensively trumped by just having a powerful enough server to handle it all with some headroom for contingency.",
